Breathe deep with your copy of The Sleepy Pebble and Other Stories 💙
~
Written by sleep specialist Professor Alice Gregory and children’s author Christy Kirkpatrick, The Sleepy Pebble combines five calming short stories with a series of techniques to help your child relax at bedtime
~
Buy now from FlyingEyeBooks.com, or from your local best bookshop ✨
For a love that knows no bounds this #ValentinesDay, look to Monty & the Poodles by @katie.harnett 💕

ANNOUNCING... brand new for you this April, I Ate Sunshine For Breakfast by Michael Holland & @pilipo_ ! 🌻
~
Enter the incredible world of plants to learn all about the green machines of the natural world. This wonderful non-fiction book will show you the powerful science going on in every leaf, petal and stem - making you look at plants in an entirely different way 🍃
~
A comprehensive guide that covers everything from parts of the plant to conservation, the also features DIY projects for young gardeners. Available for preorder on our site or any other major online retailer
~
#childrensbooks #kidsnonfiction #nature #childrensbookillustration #flyingeyebooks

Undoubtedly the most famous mountain on Earth, learn all about the history and mysteries of Everest in this gorgeously illustrated book by @liskfeng & Sangma Francis 🏔
~
Out now in the US, UK and Canada

One Day on our Blue Planet: In the Ocean by @ellastration is out in paperback TODAY 🐬🌊
~
Join this adorable dolphin calf as she explores the Pacific Ocean with her mother, and see what a day is like beneath the waves
~
Available in the UK today in bookshops everywhere, and online at FlyingEyeBooks.com

Whilst you’re getting ready for the next in the Professor Astro Cat series, why not take a gaze at Stargazing - @dominicwalliman and @benjinewman’s guide to the night sky and beyond 💫 ~
From scientific discoveries to the all the constellations as dreamed up by humans centuries ago, Ben Newman’s beloved illustrations bring these fascinating facts to life for young readers

In the great forested heights of the Himalayas, many species live peacefully... but their lives are changing for ever as humans cut down the trees that they call home 🌲
~
Pip and the Bamboo Path by @jessehodgsonillustration is a charming tale of perseverance, which also highlights the plight of animals who have lost their homes due to deforestation
~
Out now in the 🇬🇧, 🇺🇸 & 🇨🇦

Set in the vast open plains of Mexico, The Wolves of Currumpaw by @william.grill follows the true story of a notorious wolf pack and the man hired to track their leader. This is the tale of how one remarkable wolf changed a hunters life, and how that led to the formation of wildlife conservation societies across America...
~
Available in the 🇬🇧, 🇺🇸 & 🇨🇦
~
#illustration #wolves #conservation #picturebooks #kidsbooks #childrensbooks

Feeling those missing-Hilda blues whilst you wait for the next series of Netflix’s @hildatheseries?
~
Never fear, for we’ve got more of our blue-haired heroine for you! So far we have three tie-in titles ready to read, which expand on her adventures whilst giving a deeper insight into the #HildaFolk world. Perfect for readers aged 7 and up
~
Written by Stephen Davies and illustrated by Seaerra Miller
~
#hildatheseries #hildanetflix #lukepearson #flyingeyebooks #hildaandthenowherespace

Coming to bookshops near you this February... the paperback of One Day on our Blue Planet: In the Ocean by @ellastration!
~
A sweet yet informative series that focuses on the way our young animal friends spend a day, this instalment follows an adventurous dolphin calf as she explores the vast Pacific Ocean with her mother 🐬 ~
Charming and filled with facts, this book is a great gift for any little one with a love of nature and animals 🌊

Out this April is the delightful Mrs Bibi’s Elephant by Reza Dalvand - a fanciful tale of friendship between an eccentric lady and her beloved pet, which is as poignant as it is beautiful 💐
~
As well as being beautifully illustrated Mrs Bibi’s Elephant is a touching and important tale that teaches acceptance, love and understanding 🐘 ~
Preorder now from FlyingEyeBooks.com in the UK, or PenguinRandomHouse.com in the US and Canada 🇺🇸🇬🇧🇨🇦
~
#kidsbooks #childrensbooks #picturebook #picturebooks #picturebooksofinstagram

We were delighted to see The Immortal Jellyfish by Sang Miao mentioned recently in the @nytimes, in the article Helping Children Understand Death by Marissa Pessl
~
A thoughtful reflection upon how best to broach the difficult subject with young kids, The Immortal Jellyfish sits amongst a range of other insightful books that delicately touch on the concept of life after death
~
The Immortal Jellyfish is out now in 🇬🇧, 🇺🇸 and 🇨🇦

We’ve got a brand new book from the wonderful @owendaveydraws coming to bookshops near you this March - get ready to get Obsessive About Octopuses! 🐙
~
This gorgeously illustrated non-fiction book is full of fascinating facts about these eight-armed aliens of the deep... did YOU know that an octopus has three hearts, and a doughnut-shaped brain? 🍩
~
Preorder now from FlyingEyeBooks.com, and get your order two whole weeks before everyone else
~
#owendavey #octopus #childrensbooks #kidsbooks #illustration #naturebooks

“Easily able to become a classic, this gorgeously illustrated book conveys messages about the importance of friendship and taking the time to look at people a little deeper. Animal and story lovers will enjoy this ultimately sweet story of a Mouse named Julian and the unexpected development of a friendship with a fox”
~
Olivia Farr of YA Books Central on A Mouse Called Julian by @joetoddstanton 🦊 🐭

Get your flippers on for March 2020, when @profastrocat will be taking you to the bottom of the big blue in @dominicwalliman and @benjinewman’s Professor Astro Cat’s Deep-Sea Voyage!
~
Packed with exciting and engaging facts all about nature and exploration, join Professor Astro Cat as you learn where oceans come from, whether you CAN take a submarine to the bottom of the sea, and just what a coral reef exactly is...
~
Preorder now from FlyingEyeBooks.com, where you’ll receive your copy two whole weeks before everyone else 🙌

Dive in to your local bookshop today to get a copy of The Diver by @veci_artwork 🌊 ~
This enchanting tale sees a young girl and a penny share an unlikely dream of becoming divers - will both of them be able to achieve their dream with the power of a single wish?

Coming this February 2020... One Day on our Blue Planet: In The Ocean by @ellastration, in paperback! 🐬
~
Follow along with a young bottlenose dolphin and her mother as they bob through their day in the clear blue waters of the Pacific Ocean. This gorgeously illustrated picture book introduces you to a whole host of happily swimming creatures, both big and small 🌊
~
Preorder now on FlyingEyeBooks.com, where you’ll be able to get your copy two whole weeks early 💙

Wishing you all a bountiful and beautiful 2020 from all of us here at Flying Eye Books! Art from Jumble Wood by @helcovell 🌷
~
Jumble Wood by @helcovell is available now in all good bookshops, and at our online shop

To celebrate the approaching end of 2019 we’re back with our Staff Recs feature - where each of us here at Flying Eye put forward a book we believe could do with a little bit more loving 🥰
~
Our Marketing Manager Zoe picked Skyward by @sa.deng ✈️ ~
“A beautifully told and beautifully drawn book by the super-talented illustrator Sally Deng that tells the incredible stories of brave women that fought in the skies during WWII and broke down barriers for women today. A wonderful tribute to these ladies that would make an inspiring gift for any young girls in your life!”

To celebrate the approaching end of 2019 we’re back with our Staff Recs feature - where each of us here at Flying Eye put forward a book we believe could do with a little bit more loving 🥰
~
Emily, Senior Editor chose the One Day on our Blue Planet series by @ellastration - here’s what she had to say...
~
“I couldn’t decide on just one book, so I chose the super cute, fun and beautiful One Day series.”
~
“Full of facts and adorable animals, these books are a great first introduction to non-fiction, whilst also being perfect picture books to treasure. I mean just look at that cute little lion cub! Who can resist?”

A very happy holidays from this lovely lot, and from all of us at Flying Eye Books! 🎄

Art by @utkin1 🎁

To celebrate the approaching end of 2019 we’re back with our Staff Recs feature - where each of us here at Flying Eye put forward a book we believe could do with a little bit more loving 🥰
~
Satu, Managing Editor, picked A Mouse Called Julian by @joetoddstanton...
~
“A Mouse Called Julian just spoke to me because of its grumpy mouse protagonist who likes to spend time on their own, which I think many of us can relate to. I really enjoyed this lovely, funny, picture book about the power of friendship and being accepted for who you are, even if you are a fox who wants to eat a grumpy mouse protagonist” 🐭

Looking back on the beautiful books we’ve published in 2019, how can we forget Ancient Wonders by Iris Volant & @avaloon?
~
Ancient Wonders takes you on a journey not just across the world but through time, helping you explore the most inspiring monuments of our time, from the Hanging Gardens of Babylon to the Great Pyramid at Giza ☀️

To celebrate the approaching end of 2019 we’re back with our Staff Recs feature - where each of us here at Flying Eye put forward a book we believe could do with a little bit more loving 🥰
~
Ivanna, one of our Designers, chose Wild by @plaidemily
~
“This is the most beautifully illustrated book, with the most touching story. It’s a magical tale about a little girl who is wild and free. She knows nothing but nature from birth: birds taught her how to speak, bears taught her how to eat, foxes taught her how to play, and she was very happy like that. That is, until one day when she meets some people who find her very strange and want her to change - to talk ‘right’, eat ‘right’, or play ‘correctly’, just like them...”
